features: 【Coiled USB C Cable for Car】This USB C cable features an innovative spring coil design that is portable and tangle-free, making it easy to store and organise in the smaller spaces of a car. This feature is especially useful for charging in the car or other use scenarios to keep the space neat and tidy, free from cable clutter. Connecting your mobile device to the centre console via a cable, it is perfectly compatible with Android Auto and CarPlay, making it a great helper while driving. Note: Make sure there is a USB C port in the car for connecting the cable.

【100W Fast Charging】JSAUX USB C to USB C cable adopts PD and QC fast charging technology, supports up to 100W (20V/5A), experience lightning fast charging. It also supports 480Mb/s data sync speed. (Note: Actual charging speed depends on your device and wall charger)

【Stretchable Length】We offer two lengths of USB C coiled cable, the short cable can be stretched to about 1.2FT-3FT and the long cable can be stretched to about 1.6FT-6FT. This USB Type C cable is made of high-quality nylon braided material, which is soft and durable, and it can be quickly recovered after stretching. This good elasticity is suitable for a variety of scenarios, whether charging in the front and back seat of the car, at home, in the office or while travelling, it is very convenient.

【Wide Compatibility】JSAUX USB C to C cable is compatible with almost all USB-C devices, including mobile phones, tablets and laptops. Compatible with iPhone 15/15 Pro/15 Pro Max/15 Plus, MacBook Air/Pro, Samsung Galaxy S24 Ultra/S24+/S24/S23 Ultra/S23+/S23/S22 Ultra/S22+/S22/S21 Ultra/S21+/S21/S20/S20+/S20 Ultra/. Note 20, Pixel series, iPad Mini 6, iPad Pro, iPad Air, Steam Deck, Switch, ROG Ally, USB C car charger and more.

【Built-in E-Mark Chip】The JSAUX USBC to USB C cable features an advanced E-Mark chip designed to enhance your charging experience. It can intelligently identify the charging device and its charging power, which not only improves the charging efficiency, but also provides additional safety protection against device overcurrent and abnormal voltage. Reliable coiled USB C cable is safeguarded for devices while charging.

【What You will Get】: We offer this coiled USB C to USB C fast charging cable 2 packs with 18 months hassle-free usage and 24/7 friendly customer consultation, if you have any problem, we will solve your problem within 24 hours.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 17, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great looking aviator style cables
reviews.reviewText: I had the coiled aviator style cables on my mechanical keyboard for gaming but I noticed it had a slight lag to it. The coiled keyboard usb's might look good but are simple 3-pin uses. This type-c to type-c is 24 pins, capable of power transmission as well as high speed data. Still have to look of braided and coiled cable but zero latency. Looks really good on my desktop with the longer cable going to my GMMK Pro and the shorter hooked up to my GMMK Numpad. If you want to use it for charging it's capable of 100w, which is almost 4x's the speed of the fastest charging tech. So basically, it's future proof for at least the foreseeable future. Anything faster for data or for audio/video, I'd go with a thunderbolt but if you're just looking for a top of the line type-c charging or basic data connection, this is the next best thing. Highly recommend.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 19, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars One of mine isn't working as advertised
reviews.reviewText: Here we have a great design for USB-C power cables, but they are let down by a couple of features.First, the texture of this cable is... weird. I don't know what you'd call it, but it instantly makes your hands feel bone dry, it's like they're coated in power or something. It's not super pleasant. Second, there are no marking on the cable of it's capabilities. 3 weeks from now I'm not going to remember they are supposed to be 100W cables. I automatically knock 1 star off cables that don't carry the super important feature of having printed directly on them what they are capable of. I use a small label maker to mark all of my cables before I forget, but I shouldn't have to.The 3rd problem is, the longer cable of the two I received doesn't seem to want to provide 100W, or even 45W. When paired with a known good 100W USB-C charger and a Galaxy Tab S9, which can pull up to 45W, that cable has issues. After initially sending power it causes charging to shut down, and the tablet/power supply renegotiate the lower rating of just 15W, and then it charges the tablet at that, normally. The shorter cable runs at ~43W on the same charger/tablet, which is what I expect to see.So, minor quality control issue aside, these aren't terrible cables, but I probably won't order more of these and will keep looking for coiled cables elsewhere.
